TASK 4 :
        Imagine you want to upgrade your PC to run the latest version of FIFA smoothly. List which hardware components you would consider upgrading and explain why for each.




CPU: AMD Ryzen 5 7600X or Intel Core i5-13600K

Why: Both are incredibly fast modern processors that will easily handle the AI and physics logic of the game without breaking a sweat.



GPU: NVIDIA GeForce RTX 4060 Ti or RTX 4070 (Matte Black Edition)

Why: These cards provide massive graphical horsepower. They will easily run the newest EA SPORTS FC at max settings in 1440p resolution while keeping the frame rate incredibly smooth.



RAM: 32GB (2x16GB) Corsair Vengeance DDR5 6000MHz (Black)

Why: 32GB is plenty of memory to ensure the game never stutters. This specific kit comes in a low-profile, stealth-black design with no flashy lights.



Storage (SSD): 1TB WD_Black SN850X NVME SSD

Why: One of the fastest storage drives available. It will load Ultimate Team or Career Mode matches in just a few seconds.



Motherboard: MSI MAG B650 Tomahawk WIFI

Why: A high-quality, completely blacked-out motherboard that ties the dark, tailored aesthetic of the build together.



Case: Corsair 4000D Airflow (Charcoal Black)

Why: An elegant, minimalist dark-grey/black chassis with excellent cooling and cable management to keep the setup looking clean and sophisticated on your desk.



Power Supply: Corsair RM750e (750W, 80+ Gold)

Why: Reliable, fully modular power to keep everything running safely.
